social_posts.post_text: Look at what LeBron is doing in Year 20 man. Insane.

LeBron’s consistency is hilarious at this point.

16 years ago today, LeBron had the same stat line he had last night.

12 years ago today, LeBron played his first game in Cleveland after “The Decision.” One of the most hostile NBA environments ever. A security guard at the game that night said that the crowd was so rowdy that the game was almost called off...Apparently there were 9-volt batteries being thrown on the court. “This is the most hate I’ve seen. Ever,” he said. Imagine going through this as a 25 year old...

With the crowd raining boos every time he touched the ball, LeBron remained unphased, blocked out the noise and proceeded to torch the Cavs for 38 points in 30 minutes in a blowout win. He added 8 dimes and 5 rebounds.

(2010)

Big win last night. Bron was great. AD was unreal.
